        public void put(K key,

      • remove

        public V remove(K key)
        Searches the hash table for the entry that has the same key as the parameter. Returns the value that corresponds to that key stored in the hashtable and removes that value from the table.
        Parameters:
        K - The key that corresponds to the value.
        Returns:
        V The value with key K
